HEADWORD: Fringe tree
<hw>Fringe tree</hw>. <def>A small oleaceous tree (<spn>Chionanthus
virginica</spn>), of the southern United States, having clusters of
snow-white flowers with slender petals. It is often
cultivated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fringilla</ent>⟦br⟧
